Sports facility expert and chief executive officer (CEO) of Monimichelle, Ebi Egbe has said that his company would deliver the best ever FIFA Goal Project in Ugborodo Escarvos in Warri South local government area of Delta State. Egbe made the pledge when he accompanied the president of the Nigeria Football Federation (NFF), Amaju Melvin Pinnick on a visit to the community recently. He described the location of the project as fantastic, saying it would be nice to see football being played by the ocean.
“We are going to deliver the best ever FIFA Goal Project. It will be the first of its kind amongst the Riverine communities in the Ni- ger Delta,” Egbe said. Pinnick had during the visit so licited for the cooperation of the host community for the project.
He intimated the paramount ruler of Ugborodo community that world soccer governing body, FIFA has given approval for work to com- mence. The former CAF vice president called on the community to create a conductive environment for the con- tractor to deliver on time. On his part, the paramount ruler of Ugborodo who spoke through the chairman of the interim com- munity committee, thanked FIFA and NFF for the rare privilege and promised that all the support will be provided for the actualisation of the project.